# Aptfile — Ubuntu/Debian development server packages
#
# Install with:
#   sudo apt-get update
#   sed -E 's/[[:space:]]*#.*$//' Aptfile | awk 'NF' | xargs sudo apt-get install -y
#
# Or use the helper:
#   ~/.dotfiles/bin/install-aptfile
#
# Scope:
# - Conservative server/headless equivalent of Brewfile CLI tools.
# - Excludes macOS casks, fonts, GUI apps, Homebrew taps, and App Store tools.
# - Excludes transitional/deprecated packages and CLIs that are materially
#   fresher or safer from mise/vendor repositories.
# - Language runtimes and portable dev tools remain managed by mise.
# - Package availability varies by Ubuntu/Debian release; this targets current
#   Ubuntu LTS/newer.

