#############################################################
# Better managed by mise, vendor repos, or official releases #
#############################################################
# Keep these out of the default apt install because Ubuntu archive versions may
# be old, semantically different from Homebrew, or conflict with vendor repos.
#
# gh                    -> Linux: bin/install-linux-mise-tools; macOS: Brewfile.cli
# glab                  -> Linux: bin/install-linux-mise-tools; macOS: Brewfile.cli
# awscli                -> Linux: bin/install-linux-mise-tools; macOS: Brewfile.cli
# yq                    -> Linux: bin/install-linux-mise-tools; macOS: Brewfile.cli; Ubuntu yq is kislyuk's jq wrapper
# gitleaks              -> Linux: bin/install-linux-mise-tools; macOS: Brewfile.cli
# watchman              -> Ubuntu package is old; use upstream/vendor package if needed
# speedtest-cli         -> use Ookla's official speedtest CLI if accuracy matters
#
# Docker: prefer Docker's official apt repo on development servers:
#   docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
# Ubuntu archive alternatives if you explicitly want distro-managed Docker:
# docker.io
# docker-compose-v2
# docker-buildx
#
# Kubernetes/local cluster tools should track cluster versions closely:
# kubectl               -> Kubernetes pkgs.k8s.io repo or official binary; must be within ±1 minor of cluster
# helm                  -> official Helm repo/script or mise/aqua
# kind                  -> official release binary/go install; community apt packages may lag
# k9s                   -> GitHub release/mise/aqua
# lazydocker, dive      -> GitHub release/mise/aqua
#
# Other Homebrew-only/vendor tools:
# bun, uv, node, python, go, rust, java, lua -> mise
# yazi, navi, doggo, dua-cli, duckdb         -> mise/cargo/GitHub releases depending on host
# jira-cli, acli, krr, runpodctl, ubi        -> vendor installers or GitHub releases
# 1Password, Tailscale, ngrok                -> vendor apt repositories if needed

#############################################################
# Intentionally omitted / obsolete                          #
#############################################################
# apt-transport-https -> dummy transitional package; HTTPS is built into apt since 1.5
# telnet              -> avoid for port checks; use nc/nmap/curl/openssl instead
# net-tools           -> legacy ifconfig/netstat/route; use iproute2/ss instead
# ncat                -> overlaps with netcat-openbsd for default installs; install manually if needed
# coreutils           -> essential on Ubuntu/Debian, no need to list
# gcc/g++/make        -> pulled in by build-essential
